examples.en: This is land set aside for the public's enjoyment.
The young singer revelled in the public's admiration.
A vain effort to quell the public's fears only made matters worse.
The project is designed to play on the public's voyeuristic tendencies.
Inaccurate news reports are injurious to the public's faith in the media.
As the years went by, the public's interest in the murder case fell away.
Some say the investigation is a blind to keep the public's attention off the governor.
The new advertising campaign is an attempt to allay the public's concerns about the safety of the company's products.
If the sparse crowds are any indication of the public's interest in the presidential candidate, then his reputation obviously foregoes him.
